# Initrd Installer Notes

The generated installer artifacts are published as separate kernel and initramfs files.

## Published Artifact Names

| Target | Kernel artifact | Initramfs artifact |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Arch Linux `x86_64` | `vmlinuz-linux` | `initramfs-linux.img` |
| Arch Linux `aarch64` | `vmlinuz-linux` | `initramfs-linux.img` |
| CachyOS `x86_64_v3` | `vmlinuz-linux-cachyos` | `initramfs-linux-cachyos.img` |
| CachyOS `x86_64_v4` | `vmlinuz-linux-cachyos` | `initramfs-linux-cachyos.img` |

## Portable Installer

`portable_archlinux_installer` inspects the currently booted system and prints the commands needed to replace the active kernel and initramfs in place.

On `x86_64` it now:

- preserves the destination boot file names already in use on the machine
- keeps extra initrd entries such as CPU microcode untouched
- chooses matching published Mutuatech artifacts for Arch Linux and CachyOS automatically

Optional overrides:

```bash
PUBLISHED_TARGET_ARCH=...
PUBLISHED_KERNEL_BASENAME=...
PUBLISHED_INITRAMFS_BASENAME=...
./portable_archlinux_installer
```

## Wrapper Scripts

See [../../README](../../README) for the image-builder and publish-helper matrix.

The usual entrypoints are:

- `../../x86_64/initrd_installer/generate_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer`
- `../../aarch64/initrd_installer/generate_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer`
- `../../x86_64/initrd_installer/generate_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer`
- `../../x86_64/initrd_installer/generate_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer`
